  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Manager, Interior Design",
  "description": "<p><strong>A Day in the Life:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Develop creative design concepts and formulate project design packages using CAD, Sketchup and 3D Software</p></li><li><p>Prepare detailed design documentation, including technical drawings, specifications, and mood boards</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with contractors and vendors to ensure the successful implementation of design plans</p></li><li><p>Manage design projects from start to finish, ensuring deadlines and budgets are met</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with the wider design team to deliver cohesive, innovative interior solutions</p></li><li><p>Conduct design presentations to prospective buyers to convey design intent</p></li><li><p>Review progress on site and be responsible for design quality and experience</p></li><li><p>Perform any other ad-hoc duties<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>What We Are Looking For:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree in Interior Design or Architecture</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in the interior design industry</p></li><li><p>Experience in retail store environments and design of retail/corporate fixtures is a plus</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of design principles, design sensibility, and technical ability to develop a project from conceptualisation to execution</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in design software such as AutoCAD, SketchUp, and Adobe Creative Suite</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication and client-facing skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment</p></li><li><p>Creativity, attention to detail, and a passion for interior design</p></li></ul>",
